On november 17, 2012
Doomys

Inspired by the Continuous Championship (started on the French forums) and pickupsticks's Championship sixes, I present to you the Grand Nine Ranking.


Rules:

[1] Only armies with NINE or fewer troopers are allowed. Any army that gets a 10th trooper will be removed from the listing.

[2] To sign up add a link to your HQ page (tinyurl is allowed to help with forum formatting issues) and army name then playername afterwards. This is to make it as easy as possible for everyone else to see which army name to use to fight.

e.g. http://tinyurl.com/knife-fighters Knife Fighters / pickupsticks
LINK then ARMY NAME then / PLAYER NAME

[3] To move up the ranking, beat the person above you then post a link to the replay here. Copy and paste the list, adjusting your position, and re-post it.

[4] MAKE SURE you use the correct list from the last post in the thread. MAKE SURE nobody else has posted at the same time as you. If this happens, then edit your post to correct it. Anyone that messes up the list more than three times in a month will be penalized five places, because it's a real pain for everyone else.

[5] Only fights where you sent the challenge (are on the left) are allowed. Only direct challenge fights are allowed. Fight links that end in BAT1/BAT2/BAT3 or MISS1/MISS2/MISS3 are not eligible.

[6] A player may choose to go "inactive" by marking their army with [REST]

e.g. [REST] http://tinyurl.com/knife-fighters Knife Fighters / pickupsticks
If a player directly above you is inactive and you can beat the next player then you may skip the inactive player.

e.g.
1) player A
2) [REST] player B
3) Player C may choose to move up into first place if they can beat player A. They cannot move into 2nd place unless they beat player B in the usual way.

[7] Only one army per player is allowed. Protecting your army with a password is highly recommended.

...that should be enough rules to keep things in order, but we all know how it works so stop reading and get fighting.

dsci
pickupsticksThe links have confused me before... someone likes to use tinyurl's that are nothing to do with the name of the army!

Actually I don't trust to any linkcutter (like tinyurl), because very often short encrypted links hide something bad like viruses, scripts, traffic-catchers, sniffers or something like that. I usually surf Ru.net, it's russian segment of world wide web, and you need keep your eyes on your links. Due to it I don't use resources like tinyurl at all and don't use short links of youtube or twitter or instagramm or other like links. I check all links I activate and due to it I never uses for fights army names - I just make copy of their first part of link

[8640217]

Let me give you some advice.
When you are organizing your troopers it helps to keep your waves balanced.
I won this battle because my waves were better balanced than your waves.
Your waves were poorly balanced because you had 8 troopers in the first wave, and only 1 trooper in the second wave.
My waves were better balanced than yours because I had 5 troopers in my first wave, and 4 in my second wave. So I basically had a fair amount of troopers in each wave.

Now let me ask you this.
If both of our waves are killed, who would suffer more? You, or me?
You would suffer more because you lost more troopers than I did.
You would lose 8 troopers while I only lose 5. So you would have more to lose than I would. That is exactly what happened in this battle, and that is exactly why you lost.

Occasionally, it will be better to have alot of troopers in your first wave to outnumber the enemies troops, but it is often better to keep your waves balanced.

Why don't you take some troopers out of your first wave and put them in your second wave so that your first and second wave can be balanced?
